<event name="LANIUS_FREE_STUFF" unique="true">
	<text>You stumble across a badly damaged Lanius craft. It jumps away as soon as it sees you. Looking around the area, you discover a number of destroyed Rebel automated ships. It must have been quite the fight. You scrap what remains.</text> 
	<autoReward level="HIGH">standard</autoReward>
</event>

<event name="LANIUS_LANGUAGE" unique="true">
	<text>A Lanius ship hails you, asking a favor. They speak your language moderately well, but it could use improvement. "Requesting, scans data, for using as improvements of translation."</text> 
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Agree, knowing it will likely take some time.</text>
		<event>
			<text>As expected, the data scans take a fair bit of time, but you can tell the Lanius are very happy. They offer to pay you.</text>
			<modifyPursuit amount="1"/>
			<choice>
				<text>Accept the pay.</text>
				<event>
					<autoReward level="MED">standard</autoReward>
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice>
				<text>Suggest the Lanius join your crew to learn even more.</text>
				<event>
					<text>The Lanius agrees to your suggestion and comes on-board.</text>
					<crewMember amount="1" class="lanius"/>
				</event>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice>
		<text>Refuse.</text>
		<event>
			<text>"Ok. Thanks many considering." They fly away, leaving you alone at the beacon.</text>
			<choice>
				<text>Do something onboard the ship.</text>
				<event load="STORAGE_CHECK"/>
			</choice>
			<choice>
				<text>Do nothing.</text>
				<event/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
</event>

<event name="LANIUS_INJURED" unique="true">
	<text>A single Lanius drifts through space. They don't seem responsive to your ship, but scans confirm that they are alive.</text>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Bring them on-board.</text>
		<event load="LANIUS_INJURED_RESCUE"/>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true" req="LIST_CREW_LANIUS">
		<text>(Lanius Crew) Assure the Lanius that you mean them no harm when you bring them on-board.</text>
		<event>
			<text>It seems the Lanius has been severely injured by something, and a good chunk of their body is missing. They probably won't live much longer, unless you can help.</text>
			<choice>
				<text>Heal them with scrap.</text>
				<event>
					<text>The Lanius melts down the metal and assimilates with it. You watch as the knife-like structures on its body slowly reform.</text>
					<item_modify>
						<item type="scrap" min="-30" max="-40"/>
					</item_modify>
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Continue.</text>
						<event>
							<text>Now fully healed, the Lanius gladly joins your crew to pay off its debt for you saving its life.</text>
							<crewMember amount="1" class="lanius"/>
						</event>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice hidden="true" req="medbay" lvl="2">
				<text>(Upg. Medbay) Heal the Lanius.</text>
				<event>
					<text>Somehow, the medbays nanobots are capable of repairing the damage to the Lanius's body. Grateful for saving its life, the Lanius joins your crew.</text>
					<crewMember amount="1" class="lanius"/>
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>There's nothing that can be done, let them die.</text>
				<event/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice>
		<text>Ignore the Lanius.</text>
		<event>
			<text>You ignore the Lanius and carry on with your mission.</text>
			<choice>
				<text>Do something onboard the ship.</text>
				<event load="STORAGE_CHECK"/>
			</choice>
			<choice>
				<text>Do nothing.</text>
				<event/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
</event>
