<event name="LANIUS_PUN" unique="true"> <!--the greatest event ever-->
	<text>You receive a hail from a mysterious source. A grim voice whispers to you, "knock... knock..."</text>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>W-who's there?</text>
		<event>
			<text>"L..a...n...i...u...s..."</text>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Lanius who?</text>
				<event>
					<text>"Lanius phyxiate you!" You hear the distinct sound of crew teleporting aboard!</text>
					<boarders min="2" max="2" class="lanius"/>
				</event>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
</event>

<event name="LANIUS_CONFUSED" unique="true">
	<text>You hear several thunks on your hull, followed by scraping. Scans show Lanius have landed on the ship and are now eating their way through the hull!</text>
	<choice hidden="true" req="LIST_CHECK_ANY_CREW" blue="false" lvl="1">
		<text>Send out a crewmember to try and communicate.</text>
		<event>
			<text>One of your crew, clad in a space suit reserved only for situations like this, heads out the airlock to communicate with the Lanius. The Lanius are shocked to see someone else. "You look like boat from trash? Usual junk when eat." It seems they mistook your ship as a wreck.</text>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Assure them that you aren't a wreck.</text>
				<event load="LANIUS_CONFUSED_EXPLAIN"/>
			</choice>
			<choice hidden="true" req="LIST_CREW_LANIUS">
				<text>(Lanius Crew) Have your Lanius explain.</text>
				<event>
					<text>The Lanius apologize for their misunderstanding. Most of them detach from your ship and float away into the vacuum of space, but one Lanius does not wish to go with the others. Instead, they desire to stay with your crew.</text>
					<crewMember amount="1" class="lanius"/>
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>This isn't worth our time. Just fight them off.</text>
				<event>
					<text>It doesn't take long for the Lanius to make their way into the body of the ship. Prepare to defend the ship!</text>
					<boarders min="2" max="3" class="lanius"/>
					<damage amount="0" system="random" effect="breach"/>
					<damage amount="0" system="random" effect="breach"/>
				</event>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Get ready to fight!</text>
		<event>
			<text>It doesn't take long for the Lanius to make their way into the body of the ship. They're somehow surprised to see crew onboard, but that doesn't stop them from attacking!</text>
			<boarders min="2" max="3" class="lanius"/>
			<damage amount="0" system="random" effect="breach"/>
			<damage amount="0" system="random" effect="breach"/>
		</event>
	</choice>
</event>
<eventList name="LANIUS_CONFUSED_EXPLAIN">
	<event>
		<text>Your explanation seems to be making sense to the Lanius. "Ship... not trash? Leave." The Lanius wave to you as they detach from your ship and begin to drift off into the vacuum of space once again.</text>
	</event>
	<event>
		<text>Your explanation is pointless. The Lanius are only more confused and ignore your crew, going back to salvaging your ship. You have no choice but to fight them off.</text>
