<event name="DISTRESS_LANIUS_FEEDING" unique="true">
	<text>A distressed Slug captain hails you while a Lanius ship has attached itself to the top of the Slug vessel and is slowly melting down the hull. "Could you do ussss a favor and pleasssse tell the Laniussss not to eat usss? We tried ourssselvessss but they would not ressspond. It would be greatly appreccciated."</text>
	<distressBeacon/>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Chase off the Lanius ship.</text>
		<event>
			<text>To your surprise the Lanius ship refuses to detach from the Slug's hull, rather dragging them along with it. Signs detect the Lanius are trying to jump away. If they manage to jump, they'll likely cause extreme damage to the Slug ship, if not completely destroying it.</text>
			<ship load="SHIP_LANIUS_FEEDING" hostile="true"/>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Continue...</text>
				<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true" req="LIST_CREW_LANIUS">
		<text>(Lanius Crew) Have your Lanius convince them to let the Slugs go.</text>
		<event>
			<text>Reluctantly, the Lanius ship detaches from the Slugs and flies away. That was easy...</text>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Contact the Slug ship.</text>
				<event>
					<text>Before the Slugs can even respond, the Lanius ship returns, weapons blazing. It blasts its way through the Slug ship and attacks you next.</text>
					<ship load="SHIP_LANIUS_FIGHT" hostile="true"/>
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Continue...</text>
						<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Have fun with that.</text>
		<event>
			<text>You bid the Slugs farewell and leave them to dealing with the Lanius.</text>
			<choice>
				<text>Do something onboard the ship.</text>
				<event load="STORAGE_CHECK"/>
			</choice>
			<choice>
				<text>Do nothing.</text>
				<event/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
</event>
<event name="DISTRESS_LANIUS_FEEDING_WIN">
	<text>"Thank you for your assssissstanccce, I don't know if we could have gotten out of that one otherwissse. Accccept thisss asss a gift."</text>
	<weapon name="RANDOM"/>
</event>

<event name="DISTRESS_LANIUS_FIGHT" unique="true">
	<text>You immediately do a short-range scan after arriving at the beacon. It appears to be coming from a small civilian vessel under fire from a Lanius ship. Not all Lanius are content with simply scavenging the wrecks of previous battles.</text>
	<distressBeacon/>
	<ship load="SHIP_LANIUS_CIVILIAN" hostile="false"/>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Fight the Lanius ship.</text>
		<event>
			<text>You move in to intercept the ship. Detecting a greater threat, the Lanius prepare to fight.</text>
			<ship hostile="true"/>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Continue...</text>
				<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Avoid the conflict.</text>
		<event>
			<text>Your crew seems unhappy to leave the civilians to such a fate but you try to convince them of the greater good. You don't speak of your own misgivings, however.</text>
			<choice>
				<text>Do something onboard the ship.</text>
				<event load="STORAGE_CHECK"/>
			</choice>
			<choice>
				<text>Do nothing.</text>
				<event/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true" req="LIST_CREW_LANIUS">
		<text>(Lanius Crew) Have your crew admonish their captain.</text>
		<event load="DISTRESS_LANIUS_FIGHT_LANIUS"/>
	</choice>
</event>
<eventList name="DISTRESS_LANIUS_FIGHT_LANIUS">
	<event>
		<text>After a discussion that your translator fails to comprehend, the enemy ship powers down its weapons. You learn that your crewmember successfully reminded them of their treatise promising to leave the property of sentient aliens alone. If this is a widespread rule of this race, there appear to be many who disagree with it. You attempt to hail the civilian ship now that it's safe.</text>
		<choice hidden="true">
			<text>Continue...</text>
			<event load="SAVE_CIVILIAN_LIST"/>
		</choice>
	</event>
	<event>
		<text>The ship refuses all hails, even from one of its own kind. It appears to have gone completely rogue. Before you can react, it begins to target your ship. Prepare for a fight.</text>
		<ship hostile="true"/>
		<choice hidden="true">
			<text>Continue...</text>
			<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
		</choice>
	</event>
</eventList>

<event name="DISTRESS_LANIUS_EMPTY" unique="true">
	<text load="TEXT_DISTRESS_LANIUS_EMPTY"/>
	<distressBeacon/>
	<choice>
		<text>Do something onboard the ship.</text>
		<event load="STORAGE_CHECK"/>
	</choice>
	<choice>
		<text>Do nothing.</text>
		<event/>
	</choice>
</event>
<textList name="TEXT_DISTRESS_LANIUS_EMPTY">
	<text>Whatever was the original source of the distress beacon, it has since been removed. Likely a gruesome fate at the hands of the Lanius, if you had to guess.</text>
	<text>When you get to the beacon you quickly try to locate the source of the distress call. As you are looking, the signal blinks out. It is then that you notice the small fleet of scavenger ships absorbing debris from a large battle nearby. You can't help but wonder where the distress signal came from, but you decide not to risk pressuring the fleet.</text>
</textList>

<event name="DISTRESS_LANIUS_TRAP" unique="true">
	<text>You are too late - whatever once was emitting the distress signal from this system drew a Lanius ship as well as your own. Having consumed the original target, the Lanius turn their attention to your vessel.</text>
	<ship load="SHIP_LANIUS_FIGHT" hostile="true"/>
	<distressBeacon/>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Continue...</text>
		<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
	</choice>
</event>

<event name="DISTRESS_LANIUS_SLUG" unique="true">
	<text>The distress signal from this system is coming from a Slug vessel under attack by the Lanius! The Slugs beg for assistance as the Lanius tear into their hull plating.</text>
	<distressBeacon/>
	<choice>
		<text>Attack the Lanius ship.</text>
		<event>
			<text>You prepare to attack the Lanius.</text>
			<ship load="DISTRESS_LANIUS_SLUG_SHIP" hostile="true"/>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Continue...</text>
				<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice>
		<text>Leave the Slugs to their fate.</text>
		<event>
			<text>You leave the Lanius ship alone, and prepare to jump to the next beacon.</text>
			<choice>
				<text>Do something onboard the ship.</text>
				<event load="STORAGE_CHECK"/>
			</choice>
			<choice>
				<text>Do nothing.</text>
				<event/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
</event>
<eventList name="LANIUS_SLUG_DISTRESS_END">
	<event>
		<text>The Slugs, taking advantage of the firefight, have fled the system. So much for gratitude.</text>
	</event>
	<event>
		<text>The Slugs reluctantly thank you for your help, protest they had the whole situation under control, attempt to make you pay for them helping you, and an hour later, finally relent and give you some supplies.</text>
		<autoReward level="MED">standard</autoReward>
	</event>
</eventList>

<event name="DISTRESS_LANIUS_MANTIS" unique="true">
	<text>The Mantis ship in this system looks like its distress beacon is malfunctioning... likely due to the Lanius ship mining their hull and sub-systems! It doesn't look like the Mantis ship will last much longer.</text>
	<distressBeacon/>
	<choice>
		<text>Attack the Lanius ship.</text>
		<event>
			<text>The Lanius don't seem to have noticed you yet - but they will. Launching into the fray, you target the Lanius vessel!</text>
			<ship load="DISTRESS_LANIUS_MANTIS_SHIP" hostile="true"/>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Continue...</text>
				<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice>
		<text>Leave the Mantis to their fate.</text>
		<event>
			<text>The Mantis ship is quickly overcome by the Lanius vessel, and you move away as the Lanius feed on the remains.</text>
			<choice>
				<text>Do something onboard the ship.</text>
				<event load="STORAGE_CHECK"/>
			</choice>
			<choice>
				<text>Do nothing.</text>
				<event/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
</event>
<eventList name="LANIUS_MANTIS_DISTRESS_END">
	<event>
		<text>The Mantis hiss and click, angry at being saved, and angry at themselves for needing to be saved. They part ways with some scrap metal that is no longer attached to their hull and a few missiles they can no longer use.</text>
		<autoReward level="MED">missiles</autoReward>
	</event>
	<event>
		<text>The Mantis ship has sustained too much damage - there are no survivors. You gather what resources you can from the wreckage.</text>
		<autoReward level="MED">standard</autoReward>
	</event>
