<event name="QUEST_LANIUS_ZOLTAN_PEACE">
	<text>Things don't seem to be going well at the Zoltan's destination. You must be a little late, because the Zoltan are trying desperately to negotiate with the Lanius while they draw closer like predator to their prey.</text>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Just wait and watch.</text>
		<event>
			<text>The Zoltan leader speaks slowly to the Lanius, as if that will help them understand. "Hello, my metal friends. We have brought you a wonderful proposition for peace. We request full access to all territory in your sector, the rights to all of your trade routes, etc, in return for the nobility of being allied with the Zoltan rac-" the Zoltans are cut off when one of the Lanius grows bored and fires a missile launcher straight into their engines, destroying the ship. Chaos ensues, and you figure it's time that you leave.</text>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>You were given a job. Protect the Zoltan.</text>
		<event>
			<text>It doesn't take much longer for the Lanius to turn hostile. You swoop in to defend your 'employers'.</text>
			<ship load="SHIP_PEACE_LANIUS" hostile="true"/>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Continue...</text>
				<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Those Zoltans were jerks, fight them off with the Lanius.</text>
		<event>
			<text>The Lanius might not be accustomed to the traditions and language of the other races of the galaxy, but they aren't stupid. Whatever these Zoltans want to negotiate isn't in the Lanius's bests interests, and you've decided to take a stand.</text>
			<ship load="SHIP_PEACE_ZOLTAN" hostile="true"/>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Continue...</text>
				<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
</event>
<event name="LANIUS_ZOLTAN_PEACE_ZOLTAN_WIN"> <!--you kill the zoltan-->
	<text>The Lanius ship appears to be an Elite, though its received critical damage. "Federation... savior. Recruitment, option, yes?" It seems the captain wants to work on your ship, given their ship is near destruction and the Zoltans have proven an unsatisfactory ally.</text>
	<crewMember amount="1" class="lanius_welder">Solaris</crewMember> <!--mr. schism creator man, the lanius based overhaul laythe came from-->
</event>
<event name="LANIUS_ZOLTAN_PEACE_LANIUS_WIN"> <!--you kill the lanius-->
	<text>"You have performed... Satisfactory at protecting our squadron. Though you were far from perfect, I do not have the time to fully evaluate your performance. I shall pay you adequately, but do try harder next time, should this situation arise again."</text>
	<autoReward level="HIGH">standard</autoReward>
</event>

