<event name="QUEST_BEACON_EATER">
	<preventQuest/>
	<preventFleet/>
	<quest>
		<nebulaBeacon>false</nebulaBeacon>
		<aggressive>2</aggressive>
	</quest>
	<img back="BACK_EVENT_SWARMHOME" planet="NONE"/>
	<beaconType id="map_icon_swarm" global="true">
		<color r="255" g="255" b="255" a="1.0"/>
	</beaconType>
	<text>You've certainly found... something. A humongous artificial mass of garbage hastily thrown together from millions of tons of scrap metal hosts a swarm of Lanius, flickering about like bees in a beehive. None of the ships pay you any mind, but rather carry with them heaps of metal to add to the structure. In the center of the massive sphere between it all, you notice a much more refined vessel of gigantic proportions.</text>
	<ship load="SHIP_BEACON_EATER" hostile="false"/>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Approach.</text>
		<event>
			<text>A crackling sound screams through your intercom, followed by a robotic voice. It seems they have a much better translator, because you can actually understand what they're saying, minus some grammar issues. "Pestulent outsider. Our kind endured millenia of suffering under the Forefathers, and stand here triumphant. Still, you learn not to grant us the space and respect of the last standing elder race? Get OUT of my territory, or I will tear apart your puny bodies like your invasive beacons I devour."</text>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>This guy and his swarm are a threat, and we need to destroy them.</text>
				<event>
					<text>You raise the weapons and attack the Beacon Eater. Indignant towards you for attacking, the cruiser lurches forward to meet you. "If this is your choice, be it so. I will look forward to your death."</text>
					<ship hostile="true"/>
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Continue...</text>
						<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Try to negotiate with them to stop eating beacons.</text>
				<event>
					<text>You try in vain to negotiate with the Beacon Eater. "You are deaf? Unclog ears and listen to words I am saying. This sector belongs to my people. You are invaders. Pests. If you desire your own extermination so much, then I will appease you."</text>
					<ship hostile="true"/>
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Continue...</text>
						<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice>
		<text>Dear god, this thing is huge. We have to leave.</text>
		<event/>
	</choice>
</event>
<event name="BEACON_EATER_WIN">
	<text>As the Beacon Eater falls, defeated, the entire swarm around you freezes in apprehension. In one last desperate effort, the Beacon Eater claws his way through your airlocks, dragging his deteriorating body towards you. "I... I have lived longer than your species has been alive. Yet, this is how I dying? Pity..."</text>
	<variable name="ach_boss_beaconeater" op="set" val="1"/>
	<choice hidden="true" req="BEACON_PARTS" blue="false">
		<text>We still have the beacon parts. Give them to him.</text>
		<event>
			<text>The Beacon Eater assimilates the part into his body, healing rapidly. "You... you have saved me. This is unusual mercy." The elder Lanius attempts to stand as his body continues to take back its original shape. "I have never known such gratitude of outsiders. The Forefathers... they never would have done the same."</text>
			<remove name="BEACON_PARTS"/>
			<variable name="ach_crew_beacon" op="set" val="1"/>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>The Forefathers?</text>
				<event>
					<text>"I dare not speak their name. Long ago, there were 5 ancient empires. The Imperials, the Dynasty, the Swarm, the Utopians, and... the Forefathers. They made the technology you use to lay war on existence. In the end, they destroy themselves and nearly all other empires. Only the great Swarm resist them! In my immortality I have lived through the worst of those days. It is where I have learned to trust none but my own. If all kinds tended to themselves, and themselves only, war there wouldn't be."</text>
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Sounds like what the Rebels want.</text>
						<event load="BEACON_EATER_REWARD_SAVE"/>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>He won't last long, just put him out of his misery.</text>
		<event>
			<text>A blaster charge to the back of the head is all it takes to finish off the once threatening King of the Lanius. The Lanius ships outside stir once again, and you receive several hails at once.</text>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Respond.</text>
				<event load="BEACON_EATER_REWARD"/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
</event>
<event name="BEACON_EATER_REWARD">
	<text>It seems the entire swarm had been watching the spectacle. "Outsider King murder! Bow, bow!" You can't stay for long, but accept the tribute from the concerned Lanius and hope that this victory will be enough to discourage the ravaging of Union settlements a little longer.</text>
	<unlockCustomShip silent="false">PLAYER_SHIP_LANIUS</unlockCustomShip>
	<autoReward level="HIGH">standard</autoReward>
	<weapon name="RANDOM"/>
</event>
<event name="BEACON_EATER_REWARD_SAVE">
	<text>"You compare me to the visions of the great tyrant Wentworth? I am insulted; had you not bested me here, dead you would be now. My ship... it is in ruins. I have a great debt to pay off, and an insatiable curiosity. I will journey with you and see if your people are worthy. If you are truly different from the Forefathers. Perhaps... perhaps we can yet find truce."</text>
	<crewMember amount="1" class="unique_eater" all_skills="1">Beacon Eater</crewMember>
	<unlockCustomShip silent="false">PLAYER_SHIP_LANIUS</unlockCustomShip>
	<autoReward level="HIGH">standard</autoReward>
	<weapon name="RANDOM"/>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Continue...</text>
		<event/>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Ask about the strange Lanius ship you saw earlier.</text>
		<event>
			<text>You explain to the Beacon Eater the origins of the gift. "Hmm... the Anointed returns. Long ago, my people had great schism. In the end, two halves were made. The repugnant 'Augmented' left on a great exodus to harness the power of the Forefathers. The rest, pure and clear minded, remained loyal to me. We do not speak of them unless we must. Be fortunate it is you who carried this gift. If it were them, I would have waged a war so great it would tear the galaxy in half. How dare she try to settle such irreconciliable differences."</text>
		</event>
	</choice>
</event>
